<p>If only Pirate 1 is left, he will get all 1000 coins.</p>
<pre>
Pirate 1 -&gt; 1000
Pirate 2 -&gt; X
Pirate 3 -&gt; X
Pirate 4 -&gt; X
Pirate 5 -&gt; X
</pre>

<p>If Pirates 1 and 2 left, Pirate 1 will not accept any proposal because he he knows that if he rejects Pirate 2â€™s proposal, Pirate 2 will be thrown overboard and Pirate 1 will get all 1000 coins.  Pirate 2 is doomed to get nothing.</p>
<pre>
Pirate 1 -&gt; 1000
Pirate 2 -&gt; X
Pirate 3 -&gt; X
Pirate 4 -&gt; X
Pirate 5 -&gt; X
</pre>

<p>If Pirates 1, 2, and 3 are left, Pirate 3 will offer Pirate 2 one coin and give himself the rest.  Pirate 2 will accept knowing that if he rejects then he will get nothing.  Pirate 3 will also accept, so it will be accepted by a majority.</p>
<pre>
Pirate 1 -&gt; 0
Pirate 2 -&gt; 1
Pirate 3 -&gt; 999
Pirate 4 -&gt; X
Pirate 5 -&gt; X
</pre>

<p>If Pirates 1, 2, 3, and 4 are left, Pirate 4 will offer Pirate 1 1, Pirate 2 2, and give himself the rest.</p>
<pre>
Pirate 1 -&gt; 1
Pirate 2 -&gt; 2
Pirate 3 -&gt; 0
Pirate 4 -&gt; 997
Pirate 5 -&gt; X
</pre>

<p>If Pirates 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 are left, Pirate 5 will offer:</p>
<pre>
Pirate 1 -&gt; 2
Pirate 2 -&gt; 0
Pirate 3 -&gt; 1
Pirate 4 -&gt; 0
Pirate 5 -&gt; 997
</pre>

